Add per-step model selection (provider + exact model id)

Each pipeline/project step can now pin its own AI provider and exact model id
(cheap-draft / premium-edit in one pipeline), not just route by task tier.

- ProjectStep.modelOverride { provider, model? } (blank model = provider only).
- AIRouter: CompletionRequest.model; complete() dispatches with a provider
  clone whose model is the override (every completeX method picks it up).
  Unset = provider default (unchanged behavior).
- handleMessage: new 7th overrideModel param, passed to complete().
- routes/_shared.ts stepRouting(): precedence step override -> project
  preferredProvider -> tier routing; applied at the primary/continuation/
  quality-retry executors (projects.routes.ts) and the goal-engine path
  (index.ts). 'general' short-retries stay unpinned so they can fall back.
- New endpoint POST /api/projects/:id/steps/:stepId/model -> ProjectEngine
  .setStepModelOverride(); provider validated (incl. openrouter), model id
  free-text but length-capped + control-char rejected.
- Dashboard: per-step provider dropdown ("Inherit" + 6 providers) + optional
  model-id input in the project-detail view; POSTs on change, no re-render.

Incidental fix: the dashboard execution paths passed no provider to
handleMessage, so the project-level "AI Model" override (create modal) was
ignored on dashboard runs; stepRouting's project fallback now makes it work.

Follow-up: estimatedCost still uses the base provider's placeholder rates for
an overridden model (real per-model pricing is a separate item).

Verified: tsc --noEmit clean; npm test green (29 unit + API + smoke); live
e2e (create -> set -> persist -> clear -> delete) passed.
